clinical_particulars.therapeutic_indications: For use in the treatment of atrophic vaginitis and kraurosis vulvae

contraindications.disease: Symptoms of overdose include nausea and vomiting and withdrawal bleeding may occur in females
contraindications.pharmacodynamics: Estrogens diffuse into their target cells and interact with a protein receptor Target cells include the female reproductive tract the mammary gland the hypothalamus and the pituitary Estrogens increase the hepatic synthesis of sex hormone binding globulin SHBG thyroid binding globulin TBG and other serum proteins and suppress follicle stimulating hormone FSH from the anterior pituitary The combination of an estrogen with a progestin suppresses the hypothalamic pituitary system decreasing the secretion of gonadotropin releasing hormone GnRH
